
[1]bbarbarism

   B'BARBARISM, n. [L. Barbarisums. See Barbarian.]

   1. An offense against purity of style or language; any form of speech
   contrary to the pure idioms of a particular language.

   2. Ignorance of arts; want of learning.

   3. Rudeness of manners; savagism; incivility; ferociousness; a savage
   state of society.

   4. Brutality; cruelty; barbarity. [In this sense little used, being
   superseded by barbarity.]
